- General. Good to see you.

516
00:50:00.247 --> 00:50:03.270
Our exoskeleton's got real firepower.
General Slocum.

517
00:50:03.295 --> 00:50:07.716
Well. if it does what you say it can.
I'll sign that contract tomorrow.

518
00:50:09.857 --> 00:50:10.853
He's clear! Let's go!

519
00:50:10.877 --> 00:50:13.113
I assume you're confident about this test?

520
00:50:13.138 --> 00:50:15.521
Absolutely. 
Captain Curtis is our top pilot.

521
00:50:16.120 --> 00:50:18.950
Now. what about
your commitment to OSCORP?

522
00:50:19.008 --> 00:50:22.929
Nothing would please me more than
to put Norman Osborn out of business.

523
00:50:25.359 --> 00:50:27.935
Preflight complete. Mark.

524
00:50:32.529 --> 00:50:35.216
We are picking up an unidentified object 
closing fast.

525
00:50:35.248 --> 00:50:36.553
What the hell is that?

526
00:50:36.578 --> 00:50:38.080
Can you see anything?

527
00:50:38.484 --> 00:50:39.779
Oh. my God!

528
00:50:50.217 --> 00:50:52.450
- Say "chess".
- Chess!

529
00:50:53.554 --> 00:50:54.935
Peter!

530
00:50:55.639 --> 00:50:59.677
Darling. I'm so proud of you.
You looked so handsome up there.

531
00:50:59.682 --> 00:51:01.293
Pete. good news.

532
00:51:01.318 --> 00:51:03.997
My father got the place in New York.
so we're all set this fall.

533
00:51:04.022 --> 00:51:05.771
- Oh. that's great!
- You made it.

534
00:51:08.146 --> 00:51:10.818
It's not the first time
I've been proven wrong.

535
00:51:12.948 --> 00:51:15.117
- Congratulations.
- Thanks. Dad.

536
00:51:15.611 --> 00:51:18.521
Peter. the science award. That's terrific.

537
00:51:18.546 --> 00:51:19.839
Yeah.

538
00:51:22.830 --> 00:51:26.436
I know this has been
a difficult time for you.

539
00:51:26.461 --> 00:51:29.114
but I want you to try to enjoy this day.

540
00:51:29.836 --> 00:51:35.676
Commencement: The end of one thing.
the start of something new.

541
00:51:37.590 --> 00:51:39.810
I don't want to be with you anymore.

542
00:51:39.835 --> 00:51:41.241
Here's your ring.

543
00:51:42.144 --> 00:51:44.021
You know what? Whatever.

544
00:51:44.508 --> 00:51:45.968
Your loss.

545
00:51:46.645 --> 00:51:50.419
You're like a brother to Harry.
That makes you family.

546
00:51:50.444 --> 00:51:53.411
And if you ever need anything.
just give me a call.

547
00:52:08.005 --> 00:52:09.810
Can I fix you something?

548
00:52:10.479 --> 00:52:11.980
No. thanks.

549
00:52:56.758 --> 00:52:58.968
I missed him a lot today.

550
00:53:01.445 --> 00:53:03.091
I know.

551
00:53:04.807 --> 00:53:06.642
I miss him too.

552
00:53:08.417 --> 00:53:10.599
But he was there.

553
00:53:13.941 --> 00:53:19.466
I can't help thinking about
the last thing I said to him.

554
00:53:19.491 --> 00:53:24.413
He tried to tell me something important.
and I threw it in his face.

555
00:53:26.132 --> 00:53:28.218
You loved him...

556
00:53:29.918 --> 00:53:32.146
...and he loved you.

557
00:53:33.053 --> 00:53:39.654
He never doubted the man you'd grow into.
How you were meant for great things.

558
00:53:40.865 --> 00:53:43.200
You won't disappoint him.

559
00:54:16.753 --> 00:54:21.069
<i>With great power 
comes great responsibility.</i>

560
00:54:21.094 --> 00:54:24.306
<i>Remember that. Pete. Remember that.</i>

561
00:54:34.316 --> 00:54:35.567
Hurry up!

562
00:54:47.899 --> 00:54:51.652
This is not a man. My brother saw him
building a nest in Lincoln Center.

563
00:54:51.875 --> 00:54:55.087
I think he's human. a man.
Could be a woman.

564
00:54:59.025 --> 00:55:01.778
Bobby. Get a load of this!

565
00:55:05.097 --> 00:55:09.568
He throws up his hands.
ropes come out. and he climbs up them.

566
00:55:09.593 --> 00:55:13.914
I see the web. his signature.
and I know Spider-Man was here.

567
00:55:13.939 --> 00:55:16.708
The guy protects us. protects the people.

568
00:55:16.733 --> 00:55:19.560
Some kind of freakyloo or something.

569
00:55:19.585 --> 00:55:21.629
He stinks and I don't like him.

570
00:55:22.406 --> 00:55:23.991
Don't move. lady!

571
00:55:32.027 --> 00:55:34.780
Guy with eight hands. Sounds hot.

572
00:55:34.805 --> 00:55:37.083
He had those tights and that tight little-

573
00:55:37.108 --> 00:55:40.614
Dresses like a spider 
He looks like a bug

574
00:55:40.843 --> 00:55:44.596
But we should all just give him
One big hug

575
00:55:44.797 --> 00:55:49.385
Look out 
Here comes the Spider-Man

576
00:55:53.103 --> 00:55:56.779
"Who is Spider-Man?"
He's a criminal. that's who he is.

577
00:55:57.023 --> 00:56:01.044
A vigilante. a public menace.
What's he doing on my front page?

578
00:56:01.069 --> 00:56:03.161
Mr. Jameson. your wife's on line 1.
She needs to know-

579
00:56:03.280 --> 00:56:04.826
Mr. Jameson. there's a page six problem.

580
00:56:04.831 --> 00:56:06.631
We have a page one problem. Shut up.

581
00:56:06.656 --> 00:56:08.529
- Well?
- He's news.

582
00:56:08.554 --> 00:56:10.431
They are really important clients.
They can't wait.

583
00:56:10.455 --> 00:56:11.263
They're about to.

584
00:56:11.288 --> 00:56:13.587
He pulled six people off that subway.

585
00:56:13.620 --> 00:56:15.417
Sure. from a wreck he probably caused.

586
00:56:15.446 --> 00:56:17.775
Something goes wrong and 
this creepy crawler is there. Look at that.

587
00:56:17.799 --> 00:56:19.771
He's fleeing the scene. 
What's that tell you?

588
00:56:19.796 --> 00:56:23.901
He's probably going to save
somebody else. He's a hero!

589
00:56:23.926 --> 00:56:26.862
Then why is he wearing a mask?
What's he got to hide?

590
00:56:26.887 --> 00:56:29.932
She just needs to know
if you want chintz or chenille.

591
00:56:29.957 --> 00:56:31.044
Whichever's cheaper.

592
00:56:31.054 --> 00:56:32.701
Mr. Jameson. it's like this:

593
00:56:32.726 --> 00:56:36.563
We double-booked page six.
Macy's and Conway's both have...

594
00:56:36.588 --> 00:56:39.029
We sold out four printings.

595
00:56:39.314 --> 00:56:40.119
Sold out?

596
00:56:40.144 --> 00:56:41.353
Every copy.

597
00:56:42.065 --> 00:56:45.797
Tomorrow. Spider-Man. page one.
Move Conway to page seven.

598
00:56:45.822 --> 00:56:47.966
- That's a problem with page seven.
- Then make it page eight. and 10% off.

599
00:56:47.991 --> 00:56:49.345
- Make it 5%.
- That can't be done.

600
00:56:49.369 --> 00:56:50.685
Get out of here!

601
00:56:50.710 --> 00:56:52.672
Problem is we don't have a decent picture.

602
00:56:52.704 --> 00:56:55.735
Eddie's been on it for weeks.
but we can barely get a glimpse of him.

603
00:56:55.760 --> 00:56:57.825
Aw. what is he. shy?

604
00:56:58.030 --> 00:57:02.034
If we can get Julia Roberts in a thong. 
we can get a picture of this weirdo.

605
00:57:02.059 --> 00:57:05.614
On the front page:
"Cash for a Spider-Man picture."

606
00:57:05.756 --> 00:57:09.411
He doesn't want to be famous?
I'll make him infamous!

607
00:57:20.649 --> 00:57:21.680
Hey!

608
00:57:21.705 --> 00:57:23.123
Buzz off.

609
00:57:23.902 --> 00:57:25.475
M.J.. it's me. Peter.

610
00:57:25.500 --> 00:57:26.701
Hi!

611
00:57:28.534 --> 00:57:30.142
What are you doing around here?

612
00:57:30.158 --> 00:57:32.498
I'm begging for a job. How about you?

613
00:57:33.954 --> 00:57:36.342
- I'm headed to an audition.
- An audition?

614
00:57:36.703 --> 00:57:37.972
So you're acting now?

615
00:57:37.997 --> 00:57:39.040
Yeah.

616
00:57:39.065 --> 00:57:43.105
I work steady. 
In fact. I just got off a job.

617
00:57:43.130 --> 00:57:44.490
That's great. M.J.

618
00:57:44.882 --> 00:57:46.998
You're doing it. Living your dream.

619
00:57:47.023 --> 00:57:49.887
Glamour girl! Your drawer was short $6!

620
00:57:49.912 --> 00:57:52.748
Next time. I'll take it out of your check.

621
00:57:53.788 --> 00:57:57.584
Excuse me. Miss Watson?
I'm talking to you! Hey!

622
00:57:57.769 --> 00:58:00.063
Yes. Enrique! Okay? I get you.

623
00:58:00.088 --> 00:58:03.443
It better not happen no more.
Don't roll your eyes at me.

624
00:58:11.325 --> 00:58:12.803
Some dream. huh?

625
00:58:13.793 --> 00:58:16.318
It's nothing to be embarrassed about.

626
00:58:16.642 --> 00:58:19.295
- Don't tell Harry.
- Don't tell Harry?

627
00:58:19.917 --> 00:58:23.615
Don't you guys live together?
We're going out. Didn't he tell you?

628
00:58:24.922 --> 00:58:26.507
Oh. yeah. Right.

629
00:58:26.753 --> 00:58:29.985
I think he'd hate the idea
of my waiting tables.

630
00:58:30.010 --> 00:58:32.088
He'd think it was low or something.

631
00:58:32.112 --> 00:58:34.431
It's not low. You have a job.

632
00:58:34.765 --> 00:58:39.186
You know. Harry doesn't live on
a little place I like to call Earth.

633
00:58:40.604 --> 00:58:42.523
No. I guess not.

634
00:58:47.512 --> 00:58:48.779
Thanks. Pete.

635
00:58:50.421 --> 00:58:52.339
We should catch up sometime.

636
00:58:56.325 --> 00:58:58.428
Let's get some lunch some evening.

637
00:59:00.454 --> 00:59:05.145
I'll come by and have some of your
Moondance coffee some day.

638
00:59:05.170 --> 00:59:06.575
And I won't tell Harry.

639
00:59:06.585 --> 00:59:08.868
- No. Don't tell Harry.
- I won't.

640
00:59:11.428 --> 00:59:13.180
I won't tell Harry.

641
00:59:24.460 --> 00:59:25.809
Timing's perfect.

642
00:59:25.833 --> 00:59:26.921
Hey.

643
00:59:27.144 --> 00:59:29.844
Five new contracts. It'll be great.

644
00:59:32.614 --> 00:59:35.352
Norman's making his weekly inspection.

645
00:59:36.118 --> 00:59:38.370
Spent half of it on the phone.

646
00:59:38.954 --> 00:59:43.383
Look. man. I'm glad you're here.
I need your help. I'm really lost here.

647
00:59:44.501 --> 00:59:45.876
Are you all right?

648
00:59:47.129 --> 00:59:51.837
You look like you just got second place
in the science fair.

649
00:59:53.014 --> 00:59:55.985
I was late for work 
and Dr. Connors fired me.

650
00:59:56.010 --> 00:59:57.553
You were late again?

651
00:59:58.265 --> 01:00:01.508
I don't get it.
Where do you go all the time?

652
01:00:02.394 --> 01:00:03.645
Around.

653
01:00:03.812 --> 01:00:05.352
Peter Parker.

654
01:00:05.989 --> 01:00:08.562
- Maybe you'll tell me who she is.
- Who's that?

655
01:00:08.587 --> 01:00:11.087
- This mystery girl Harry's been dating.
- Dad.

656
01:00:11.987 --> 01:00:13.797
- When do I get to meet her?
- Dad!

657
01:00:13.822 --> 01:00:16.355
Well. sorry. Harry hasn't mentioned her.

658
01:00:19.995 --> 01:00:23.248
Pete. you're probably looking
for a job now. right?

659
01:00:23.273 --> 01:00:25.543
Dad. maybe you can help him out.

660
01:00:26.459 --> 01:00:28.890
I appreciate it. but I'll be fine.

661
01:00:28.917 --> 01:00:30.923
No problem. I'll make a few calls.

662
01:00:30.948 --> 01:00:35.433
No. I couldn't accept it. sir. 
I like to earn what I get. I'll find work.

663
01:00:35.458 --> 01:00:37.084
I respect that.

664
01:00:37.804 --> 01:00:39.932
You want to make it on your own.

665
01:00:40.599 --> 01:00:41.934
That's great.

666
01:00:42.784 --> 01:00:45.120
What other skills do you have. Parker?

667
01:00:45.308 --> 01:00:47.832
I was thinking of something in photography.

668
01:00:50.442 --> 01:00:51.693
Hello.

669
01:00:53.612 --> 01:00:55.793
Let's go! Move it!

670
01:00:57.074 --> 01:00:58.742
Watch the street!

671
01:01:14.174 --> 01:01:15.368
Cheese!

672
01:01:24.476 --> 01:01:25.769
They're crap.

673
01:01:25.978 --> 01:01:28.939
Crap. crap. Megacrap.

674
01:01:29.314 --> 01:01:30.769
I'll give you $200 for all of them.

675
01:01:30.793 --> 01:01:32.484
That seems a little low.

676
01:01:32.509 --> 01:01:34.249
Take them somewhere else.

677
01:01:34.278 --> 01:01:37.425
Sir. your wife says 
the tile's out of stock.

678
01:01:37.449 --> 01:01:39.053
Tell her we'll just put a rug there.

679
01:01:39.157 --> 01:01:41.118
Sit down. Give me that.

680
01:01:42.703 --> 01:01:45.389
Give you 300. 
That's the standard freelance fee.

681
01:01:45.414 --> 01:01:48.030
- Scrap page one. Run that photo instead.
- Headline?

682
01:01:48.085 --> 01:01:51.395
"Spider-Man. Hero or Menace?
Exclusive Daily Bugle Photos"

683
01:01:51.420 --> 01:01:53.573
Menace? He was protecting-

684
01:01:53.597 --> 01:01:56.225
You take the pictures. 
I'll make up the headlines. Okay?

685
01:01:56.258 --> 01:01:57.555
All right? That okay with you?

686
01:01:57.580 --> 01:01:59.382
- Yes. sir.
- Goody.

687
01:02:00.053 --> 01:02:02.936
Give this to the girl up front.
She'll see you get paid.

688
01:02:03.718 --> 01:02:06.718
- I'd like a job. sir.
- No jobs. Freelance.

689
01:02:06.792 --> 01:02:08.663
Best thing for a kid your age.

690
01:02:08.924 --> 01:02:13.220
You bring me more shots of that clown.
maybe I'll take them off your hands.

691
01:02:13.358 --> 01:02:15.382
But I never said you have a job.

692
01:02:15.398 --> 01:02:19.364
Meat. I'll send you a nice box of Christmas
meat. The best I can do. Get out of here.

693
01:02:19.389 --> 01:02:20.975
Bring me more photos.

694
01:02:22.367 --> 01:02:23.577
- Hi.
- Hi.

695
01:02:23.785 --> 01:02:26.507
Mr. Jameson told me to give that to you.

696
01:02:28.290 --> 01:02:29.995
Welcome to the Daily Bugle.

697
01:02:30.019 --> 01:02:31.350
Thank you.

698
01:02:31.960 --> 01:02:33.444
I'm Peter Parker.

699
01:02:35.839 --> 01:02:37.585
I'm a photographer.

700
01:02:38.800 --> 01:02:41.345
Yes. I can see that.

701
01:02:49.057 --> 01:02:55.275
As of today. OSCORP Industries
has surpassed Quest Aerospace

702
01:02:55.300 --> 01:02:59.137
as the principal supplier
to the United States military.

703
01:02:59.905 --> 01:03:02.870
In short. 
ladies and gentlemen of the board.

704
01:03:02.904 --> 01:03:09.289
costs are down. revenues are up.
and our stock has never been higher.

705
01:03:09.314 --> 01:03:13.735
Wonderful news. Norman.
That's why we're selling the company.

706
01:03:14.769 --> 01:03:15.785
What?

707
01:03:15.810 --> 01:03:20.778
Quest is recapitalizing in the wake
of the bombing. Expanding.

708
01:03:21.378 --> 01:03:24.131
They made a tender offer we can't ignore.

709
01:03:24.395 --> 01:03:25.656
Why wasn't I told?

710
01:03:25.681 --> 01:03:30.035
The last thing they want is a power
struggle with entrenched management.

711
01:03:30.060 --> 01:03:32.354
The deal is off if you come with it.

712
01:03:32.521 --> 01:03:35.941
The board expects your resignation
in 30 days.

713
01:03:36.227 --> 01:03:38.188
You can't do this to me.

714
01:03:41.147 --> 01:03:43.441
I started this company.

715
01:03:44.616 --> 01:03:47.035
You know how much I sacrificed?

716
01:03:50.873 --> 01:03:52.735
Oh. Max. Please.

717
01:03:52.759 --> 01:03:56.145
Norman. the board is unanimous.

718
01:03:56.879 --> 01:04:00.403
We're announcing the sale
after the World Unity Festival.

719
01:04:00.994 --> 01:04:02.496
I'm sorry.

720
01:04:03.427 --> 01:04:05.184
You're out. Norman.

721
01:04:15.462 --> 01:04:16.963
Am I?

722
01:04:21.153 --> 01:04:27.006
Welcome to OSCORP Industries' Unity Day
Festival. Let's hear it for Macy Gray.

723
01:05:04.235 --> 01:05:07.844
M.J.. why didn't you wear the black dress?

724
01:05:08.784 --> 01:05:12.454
Just. I wanted to impress my father.
He loves black.

725
01:05:12.621 --> 01:05:17.167
Well. maybe he'll be impressed
no matter what. You think I'm pretty.

726
01:05:17.661 --> 01:05:19.563
I think you're beautiful.

727
01:05:32.836 --> 01:05:36.089
Will you do me a favour?
I forgot my drink inside.

728
01:05:46.363 --> 01:05:48.664
- Oh. hi. Mr. Fargas.
- Oh. Harry.

729
01:05:49.575 --> 01:05:51.352
Have you seen my father around?

730
01:05:52.031 --> 01:05:54.797
Well. I'm not sure if he's coming today.

731
01:06:06.851 --> 01:06:09.373
- What is that?
- Must be new this year.

732
01:06:14.141 --> 01:06:15.434
What is that?

733
01:06:15.601 --> 01:06:16.951
That's our glider!

734
01:06:28.131 --> 01:06:29.590
What the hell was that?

735
01:06:57.768 --> 01:06:58.932
Code three! Code three!

736
01:07:15.202 --> 01:07:16.733
Oh. my God! Harry!

737
01:07:16.757 --> 01:07:17.542
M.J.!

738
01:07:23.335 --> 01:07:26.797
Harry! Help me! Harry!

739
01:07:32.252 --> 01:07:34.004
Out. am I?

740
01:07:38.886 --> 01:07:40.085
Mary Jane!

741
01:07:40.109 --> 01:07:40.956
Harry!

742
01:07:44.273 --> 01:07:46.149
Hello. my dear.

743
01:07:47.150 --> 01:07:48.659
It's Spider-Man!

744
01:08:00.451 --> 01:08:01.498
Come on. Move. kid.

745
01:08:01.515 --> 01:08:02.565
Come on. Billy!

746
01:08:05.961 --> 01:08:08.151
Somebody help him!

747
01:08:08.341 --> 01:08:09.682
No!

748
01:08:11.550 --> 01:08:12.768
Mommy!

749
01:08:14.923 --> 01:08:16.147
Hold it right there!

750
01:08:16.171 --> 01:08:17.206
I surrender.

751
01:08:17.417 --> 01:08:18.358
Oh. boy.

752
01:08:18.382 --> 01:08:19.761
Hold it right there!

753
01:08:25.923 --> 01:08:27.175
Impressive.

754
01:08:51.465 --> 01:08:52.621
Mary Jane!

755
01:08:52.645 --> 01:08:54.927
Help! Someone please help me!

756
01:09:20.144 --> 01:09:21.187
Hold on!

757
01:09:22.931 --> 01:09:23.973
Watch out!

758
01:09:33.131 --> 01:09:36.927
We'll meet again. Spider-Man!

759
01:10:22.431 --> 01:10:25.100
Well. beats taking the subway.

760
01:10:25.309 --> 01:10:28.224
Don't mind us.
She just needs to use the elevator.

761
01:10:28.377 --> 01:10:29.503
Wait.

762
01:10:30.022 --> 01:10:31.273
Who are you?

763
01:10:31.440 --> 01:10:33.033
You know who I am.

764
01:10:33.057 --> 01:10:34.107
I do?

765
01:10:34.132 --> 01:10:36.365
Your friendly neighborhood Spider-Man.

766
01:10:48.668 --> 01:10:52.547
Incredible?
What do you mean he's incredible?

767
01:10:53.597 --> 01:10:57.159
No. All right. wait. 
Stay there. I'll come over.

768
01:10:57.950 --> 01:10:59.619
No. I'm gonna come...

769
01:10:59.968 --> 01:11:03.388
All right. Fine.
Will you call me in the morning?

770
01:11:03.514 --> 01:11:08.503
And we'll go and have breakfast and...
I want to buy you something.

771
01:11:09.186 --> 01:11:11.925
Because I want to. 
It'll make you feel better.

772
01:11:13.565 --> 01:11:17.378
Okay. And what do you mean. incredible?

773
01:11:19.954 --> 01:11:22.331
All right. I'm sorry. Sleep tight.

774
01:11:22.616 --> 01:11:24.081
Don't let the bedbugs...

775
01:11:30.040 --> 01:11:33.085
She's all right. 
She's just a little rattled.

776
01:11:34.333 --> 01:11:37.706
Look. Pete. 
I should have told you about us.

777
01:11:39.663 --> 01:11:42.081
But you should know I'm crazy about her.

778
01:11:42.399 --> 01:11:45.128
It's just. you know.
you never made a move.

779
01:11:46.503 --> 01:11:50.362
You're right. I didn't.

780
01:11:54.515 --> 01:11:56.870
I'm gonna get some rest.

781
01:11:58.208 --> 01:12:00.461
I'm gonna stay up for a while.

782
01:12:01.475 --> 01:12:03.227
What was that thing?

783
01:12:03.936 --> 01:12:05.270
I don't know.

784
01:12:06.696 --> 01:12:09.386
Whatever it is. somebody has to stop it.

785
01:12:26.013 --> 01:12:27.180
Somebody there?

786
01:12:27.901 --> 01:12:29.808
Somebody.

787
01:12:31.240 --> 01:12:32.783
Who said that?

788
01:12:33.520 --> 01:12:36.534
Don't play the innocent with me.

789
01:12:39.318 --> 01:12:41.612
You've known all along.

790
01:12:45.991 --> 01:12:47.509
Where are you?

791
01:12:47.534 --> 01:12:51.580
Follow the cold shiver
running down your spine.

792
01:12:58.420 --> 01:12:59.433
I'm right here.

793
01:13:01.853 --> 01:13:03.495
I don't understand.

794
01:13:05.006 --> 01:13:12.159
Did you think it was coincidence? 
So many good things. all happening for you.

795
01:13:12.184 --> 01:13:15.620
All for you. Norman.

796
01:13:18.203 --> 01:13:19.621
What do you want?

797
01:13:20.359 --> 01:13:25.239
To say what you won't.
To do what you can't.

798
01:13:25.405 --> 01:13:29.628
To remove those in your way.

799
01:13:33.783 --> 01:13:35.743
The board members.

800
01:13:37.351 --> 01:13:38.651
You killed them.

801
01:13:38.676 --> 01:13:40.219
We killed them.

802
01:13:40.838 --> 01:13:41.779
We?

803
01:13:41.797 --> 01:13:46.308
Remember? 
Your little accident in the laboratory.

804
01:13:48.394 --> 01:13:50.034
The performance enhancers.

805
01:13:50.059 --> 01:13:54.941
Bingo. Me! Your greatest creation.

806
01:13:55.598 --> 01:14:02.568
Bringing you what you've always wanted: 
Power beyond your wildest dreams.

807
01:14:02.593 --> 01:14:04.965
And it's only the beginning.

808
01:14:06.573 --> 01:14:10.911
There's only one who can stop us.

809
01:14:11.641 --> 01:14:15.020
Or imagine if he joined us.

810
01:14:19.972 --> 01:14:23.184
Spider-Man. And the Green Goblin.

811
01:14:23.317 --> 01:14:26.570
The Green Goblin. You like that?
Made it up myself.

812
01:14:26.595 --> 01:14:28.500
These weirdos all got to have a name.

813
01:14:28.524 --> 01:14:29.598
Mr. Jameson. Spider-

814
01:14:29.623 --> 01:14:31.051
- Hoffman!
- Yeah?

815
01:14:32.848 --> 01:14:34.891
Call the patent office. 
Copyright the name "Green Goblin".

816
01:14:34.915 --> 01:14:36.785
I want a quarter 
every time somebody says it.

817
01:14:36.810 --> 01:14:38.512
How about "Green Meanie"?

818
01:14:38.826 --> 01:14:42.152
Spider-Man wasn't attacking the city.
he was trying to save it. That's slander.

819
01:14:42.177 --> 01:14:44.512
It is not. I resent that.

820
01:14:44.537 --> 01:14:47.387
Slander is spoken. In print. it's libel.

821
01:14:47.821 --> 01:14:49.770
You don't trust anybody.
that's your problem.

822
01:14:49.924 --> 01:14:51.676
I trust my barber.

823
01:14:52.534 --> 01:14:54.219
What are you. his lawyer? Get out of here.

824
01:14:54.244 --> 01:14:57.793
Let him sue. Get rich like a normal person.
That's what made this country-

825
01:15:06.435 --> 01:15:09.563
Jameson. you slime.

826
01:15:09.588 --> 01:15:13.305
Who's the photographer 
who takes the pictures of Spider-Man?

827
01:15:13.330 --> 01:15:15.321
I don't know. His stuff comes in the mail.

828
01:15:15.345 --> 01:15:17.301
- You're lying!
- I swear.

829
01:15:17.326 --> 01:15:19.578
He's the one who can bring me to him.

830
01:15:19.598 --> 01:15:22.674
- I don't know who he is.
- You are useless.

831
01:15:22.699 --> 01:15:24.699
Set him down. tough guy.

832
01:15:25.234 --> 01:15:26.586
Speak of the devil.

833
01:15:26.610 --> 01:15:29.434
Spider-Man! 
I knew you two were in this together! I-

834
01:15:29.655 --> 01:15:32.613
Hey kiddo. 
let Mom and Dad talk for a minute.

835
01:15:32.638 --> 01:15:34.973
Sleep...

836
01:15:49.758 --> 01:15:53.762
Wake up. little spider. Wake up.

837
01:15:53.929 --> 01:15:58.350
No. you're not dead yet.

838
01:15:58.559 --> 01:16:02.723
Just paralyzed... temporarily.

839
01:16:03.856 --> 01:16:06.942
You're an amazing creature. Spider-Man.

840
01:16:07.150 --> 01:16:09.820
You and I are not so different.

841
01:16:10.435 --> 01:16:13.926
I'm not like you. You're a murderer.

842
01:16:14.089 --> 01:16:16.967
Well. to each his own.

843
01:16:17.149 --> 01:16:20.215
I chose my path.
you chose the way of the hero.

844
01:16:20.747 --> 01:16:25.377
And they found you amusing
for a while. the people of this city.

845
01:16:25.586 --> 01:16:29.010
But the one thing 
they love more than a hero

846
01:16:29.035 --> 01:16:32.622
is to see a hero fail. fall. die trying.

847
01:16:32.985 --> 01:16:37.426
In spite of everything you've done for
them. eventually. they will hate you.

848
01:16:37.451 --> 01:16:38.599
Why bother?

849
01:16:39.025 --> 01:16:40.360
Because it's right.

850
01:16:41.215 --> 01:16:43.356
Here's the real truth.

851
01:16:43.937 --> 01:16:46.940
There are eight million people 
in this city.

852
01:16:47.332 --> 01:16:51.628
And those teeming masses exist
for the sole purpose

853
01:16:51.649 --> 01:16:55.757
of lifting the few exceptional people 
onto their shoulders.

854
01:16:55.782 --> 01:16:57.201
You. me.

855
01:16:57.635 --> 01:16:59.449
we're exceptional.

856
01:16:59.949 --> 01:17:07.402
I could squash you like a bug right now.
But I'm offering you a choice.

857
01:17:07.595 --> 01:17:12.395
Join me. 
Imagine what we could accomplish together.

858
01:17:12.420 --> 01:17:15.173
What we could create.

859
01:17:15.693 --> 01:17:17.695
Or we could destroy.

860
01:17:17.971 --> 01:17:22.655
Cause the deaths of countless innocents
in selfish battle again and again and again

861
01:17:22.680 --> 01:17:26.735
until we're both dead.
Is that what you want?

862
01:17:28.844 --> 01:17:31.157
Think about it. hero.

863
01:17:43.872 --> 01:17:48.610
In spite of everything you've done for
them. eventually. they will hate you.

864
01:17:59.513 --> 01:18:01.365
- It's me again.
- Hey.

865
01:18:01.390 --> 01:18:02.991
How was your audition?

866
01:18:03.016 --> 01:18:04.161
How'd you know?

867
01:18:04.185 --> 01:18:08.004
The hot line. Your mom...
told my aunt. told me.

868
01:18:08.605 --> 01:18:10.123
So you just came by?

869
01:18:10.148 --> 01:18:13.548
I was in the neighborhood.
Needed to see a friendly face.

870
01:18:13.881 --> 01:18:18.008
I took two buses and a cab
to get in the neighborhood. but...

871
01:18:18.727 --> 01:18:20.229
So how'd it go?

872
01:18:22.366 --> 01:18:24.952
They said I needed acting lessons.

873
01:18:25.087 --> 01:18:27.594
A soap opera told me
I needed acting lessons.

874
01:18:29.126 --> 01:18:34.714
Let me buy you a cheeseburger.
The sky's the limit. up to $7.84.

875
01:18:35.681 --> 01:18:37.767
I'd like a cheeseburger.

876
01:18:38.280 --> 01:18:41.070
Oh. but I'm going out to dinner with Harry.

877
01:18:42.034 --> 01:18:43.452
Come with us.

878
01:18:43.807 --> 01:18:46.617
No. thanks. How's it going with...

879
01:18:48.478 --> 01:18:50.981
Never mind. That's none of my business.

880
01:18:51.457 --> 01:18:52.781
It's not?

881
01:18:54.338 --> 01:18:56.006
Why so interested?

882
01:18:56.682 --> 01:18:58.183
I'm not.

883
01:18:58.488 --> 01:18:59.865
You're not?

884
01:19:01.452 --> 01:19:04.296
- Well. why would I be?
- I don't know.

885
01:19:04.408 --> 01:19:06.202
Why would you be?

886
01:19:08.081 --> 01:19:09.503
I...

887
01:19:10.521 --> 01:19:12.023
I don't know.

888
01:19:14.421 --> 01:19:16.539
Sorry you won't come with us.

889
01:19:19.718 --> 01:19:21.625
I'd better run. tiger.

890
01:19:30.187 --> 01:19:31.945
Hey. check it out. man.

891
01:19:32.564 --> 01:19:34.031
Come on. man.

892
01:19:37.653 --> 01:19:40.390
Hey. where you going. baby?
Come on!

893
01:19:58.673 --> 01:19:59.888
Get off me!

894
01:20:33.393 --> 01:20:34.614
Wait!

895
01:20:40.076 --> 01:20:42.349
You have a knack for getting in trouble.

896
01:20:42.527 --> 01:20:46.906
You have a knack for saving my life.
I think I have a superhero stalker.

897
01:20:47.037 --> 01:20:48.966
I was in the neighborhood.

898
01:20:50.627 --> 01:20:53.364
You are amazing.

899
01:20:54.244 --> 01:20:56.481
Some people don't think so.

900
01:20:58.243 --> 01:20:59.575
But you are.

901
01:20:59.814 --> 01:21:01.364
Nice to have a fan.

902
01:21:01.951 --> 01:21:04.442
Do I get to say thank you this time?

903
01:21:06.116 --> 01:21:07.388
Wait.

904
01:22:16.603 --> 01:22:18.730
Let me in! My baby's in there!

905
01:22:18.897 --> 01:22:21.024
- Let me go!
- The roof's collapsing!

906
01:22:21.191 --> 01:22:24.695
- Somebody save my baby!
- The roof's about to collapse!

907
01:22:24.778 --> 01:22:26.113
Look! Up there!

908
01:22:32.828 --> 01:22:34.663
Save my baby. please!

909
01:22:58.395 --> 01:22:59.521
No!

910
01:23:07.161 --> 01:23:09.134
It's okay. Your baby's fine.

911
01:23:09.159 --> 01:23:10.911
Oh. my baby!

912
01:23:12.326 --> 01:23:15.341
God bless you. Spider-Man. Bless you.

913
01:23:15.366 --> 01:23:17.389
Don't let him get away!

914
01:23:17.414 --> 01:23:20.809
Hold it! You're under arrest.
I'm taking you in.

915
01:23:20.834 --> 01:23:23.060
Oh. my God. 
there's somebody still up there!

916
01:23:25.318 --> 01:23:26.652
I'm going.

917
01:23:28.641 --> 01:23:30.384
I'll be here when you get back.

918
01:23:30.408 --> 01:23:31.716
Not coming back. Chief.

919
01:23:32.071 --> 01:23:33.198
Go! Go!

920
01:23:42.100 --> 01:23:43.583
Where are you?

921
01:23:45.901 --> 01:23:47.271
Where are you?

922
01:23:52.545 --> 01:23:54.325
I'm gonna get you out of here!

923
01:23:57.680 --> 01:23:59.182
It's okay.

924
01:24:06.130 --> 01:24:08.716
You're pathetically predictable.

925
01:24:08.976 --> 01:24:10.987
Like a moth to the flame.

926
01:24:11.731 --> 01:24:14.362
What about my generous proposal?

927
01:24:15.211 --> 01:24:18.048
Are you in or are you out?

928
01:24:18.433 --> 01:24:21.512
It's you who's out. Gobbie.
Out of your mind.

929
01:24:21.531 --> 01:24:23.018
Wrong answer.

930
01:24:24.815 --> 01:24:26.073
Oh. great.

931
01:25:04.940 --> 01:25:07.370
No one says no to me!

932
01:25:15.073 --> 01:25:17.121
M.J.. will you stop goofing around?

933
01:25:17.146 --> 01:25:18.494
Harry. relax.

934
01:25:21.038 --> 01:25:22.289
He's here.

935
01:25:23.081 --> 01:25:24.956
- Are you ready?
- Yeah.

936
01:25:26.355 --> 01:25:31.069
Aunt May. I'm sorry I'm late.
Work was murder.

937
01:25:31.093 --> 01:25:32.566
I picked up a fruitcake.

938
01:25:32.591 --> 01:25:35.987
Thank you. Mr. Osborn.
We're so glad you could come.

939
01:25:36.230 --> 01:25:38.424
Who is this lovely young lady?

940
01:25:38.931 --> 01:25:41.171
M.J.. I'd like you to meet my father.
Norman Osborn.

941
01:25:41.196 --> 01:25:42.924
Dad. this is Mary Jane Watson.

942
01:25:42.956 --> 01:25:44.181
- Hi.
- How do you do?

943
01:25:44.206 --> 01:25:46.497
I've been looking forward to meeting you.

944
01:25:46.522 --> 01:25:48.217
Happy Thanksgiving. sir.

945
01:25:48.241 --> 01:25:52.948
Now. where is Peter?
He'd better remember that cranberry sauce.

946
01:25:58.510 --> 01:26:01.495
Oh. that's weird.
I didn't know he was here.

947
01:26:04.990 --> 01:26:06.492
Peter?

948
01:26:14.604 --> 01:26:16.125
Is that you?

949
01:26:21.786 --> 01:26:25.320
How strange. There's nobody here.

950
01:26:32.405 --> 01:26:34.129
Bit of a slob. isn't he?

951
01:26:34.153 --> 01:26:36.578
All brilliant men are.

952
01:27:09.704 --> 01:27:10.785
Hey. everyone.

953
01:27:10.809 --> 01:27:12.232
- Oh. Peter!
- Parker.

954
01:27:12.250 --> 01:27:14.251
Sorry I'm late. It's a jungle out there.

955
01:27:14.276 --> 01:27:16.961
Had to beat an old lady with a stick
to get these Cranberries.

956
01:27:18.655 --> 01:27:19.809
Thank you.

957
01:27:19.833 --> 01:27:23.243
Now then. everybody sit down
and we can say grace.

958
01:27:26.615 --> 01:27:28.508
Here we go.

959
01:27:35.404 --> 01:27:37.922
- There we are.
- It looks delicious.

960
01:27:38.342 --> 01:27:39.420
Norman!

961
01:27:41.637 --> 01:27:43.484
Will you do the honors?

962
01:27:55.476 --> 01:27:58.344
Why. Peter. you're bleeding.

963
01:28:01.698 --> 01:28:07.037
I stepped off a curb and got clipped
by one of those bike messengers.

964
01:28:07.062 --> 01:28:08.771
Well. let me see.

965
01:28:08.956 --> 01:28:10.682
Oh. my goodness.

966
01:28:10.707 --> 01:28:13.126
- That looks awful.
- No. it's nothing.

967
01:28:13.168 --> 01:28:16.593
I'll get the first-aid kit.
Then we'll say grace.

968
01:28:16.613 --> 01:28:22.224
This is the boys' first Thanksgiving here.
and we are going to do things properly.

969
01:28:22.706 --> 01:28:25.372
How did you say that happened?

970
01:28:26.217 --> 01:28:29.833
Bike messenger. Knocked me down.

971
01:28:35.649 --> 01:28:38.416
If you'll excuse me. I got to be going.

972
01:28:38.440 --> 01:28:39.560
Wh-Why?

973
01:28:40.189 --> 01:28:43.799
Something has come to my attention.

974
01:28:43.824 --> 01:28:45.075
Are you all right?

975
01:28:45.213 --> 01:28:46.916
I'm fine. just fine.

976
01:28:46.940 --> 01:28:48.384
Thank you. Mrs. Parker.

977
01:28:48.408 --> 01:28:50.673
Everyone. Enjoy the fruitcake.

978
01:28:50.697 --> 01:28:51.727
Dad!

979
01:28:53.083 --> 01:28:55.224
Dad. what are you doing?

980
01:28:55.537 --> 01:28:57.938
I planned this so you'd meet M.J..
and now you have to leave?

981
01:28:57.963 --> 01:28:59.591
I've got to go.

982
01:28:59.965 --> 01:29:01.634
This girl is important to me.

983
01:29:01.658 --> 01:29:04.094
Harry. please. Look at her.

984
01:29:04.297 --> 01:29:08.473
You think a woman like that's sniffing
around because she likes your personality?

985
01:29:08.498 --> 01:29:09.872
What are you saying?

986
01:29:09.897 --> 01:29:11.622
Your mother was beautiful too.

987
01:29:11.647 --> 01:29:17.232
They're all beautiful until they're
snarling after your trust fund like wolves.

988
01:29:17.257 --> 01:29:18.677
You're wrong about her. Dad.

989
01:29:19.109 --> 01:29:22.462
A word to the not-so-wise
about your little girlfriend:

990
01:29:22.487 --> 01:29:25.397
Do what you need to with her.
then broom her fast.

991
01:29:36.752 --> 01:29:38.975
Thanks for sticking up for me. Harry.

992
01:29:39.505 --> 01:29:40.631
You heard?

993
01:29:41.057 --> 01:29:42.592
Everyone heard that creep.

994
01:29:42.627 --> 01:29:44.190
That creep is my father.

995
01:29:44.214 --> 01:29:46.778
If I'm lucky. 
I'll become half of what he is.

996
01:29:46.798 --> 01:29:49.281
So just keep your mouth shut 
about stuff you don't understand!

997
01:29:49.306 --> 01:29:50.670
Harry Osborn!

998
01:29:51.871 --> 01:29:53.576
I'm sorry. Aunt May.

999
01:29:56.790 --> 01:30:04.084
Spider-Man is all but invincible.
But Parker. we can destroy him.

1000
01:30:04.225 --> 01:30:05.380
I can't.

1001
01:30:05.405 --> 01:30:10.809
Betrayal must not be countenanced.
Parker must be educated.

1002
01:30:13.490 --> 01:30:14.556
What do I do?

1003
01:30:14.581 --> 01:30:18.669
Instruct him 
in the matters of loss and pain.

1004
01:30:18.694 --> 01:30:22.247
Make him suffer.
Make him wish he were dead.

1005
01:30:22.404 --> 01:30:23.490
Yes?

1006
01:30:23.515 --> 01:30:25.615
And then grant his wish.

1007
01:30:26.717 --> 01:30:27.903
But how?

1008
01:30:27.928 --> 01:30:32.224
The cunning warrior attacks
neither body nor mind.

1009
01:30:32.408 --> 01:30:33.742
Tell me how!

1010
01:30:33.762 --> 01:30:36.051
The heart. Osborn.

1011
01:30:36.076 --> 01:30:39.121
First. we attack his heart.

1012
01:30:41.108 --> 01:30:44.795
Give us this day our daily bread.
and forgive us our trespasses

1013
01:30:44.820 --> 01:30:47.781
as we forgive those
who trespass against us.

1014
01:30:48.031 --> 01:30:51.200
Lead us not into temptation.
but deliver us-

1015
01:30:59.626 --> 01:31:02.307
Deliver us...

1016
01:31:02.332 --> 01:31:03.708
Finish it!

1017
01:31:04.047 --> 01:31:07.385
- Finish it!
- ...from evil!

1018
01:31:13.682 --> 01:31:15.851
Two milligrams IV.

1019
01:31:17.667 --> 01:31:18.919
Get the BP.

1020
01:31:19.099 --> 01:31:20.346
Aunt May.

1021
01:31:20.350 --> 01:31:23.066
Is she gonna be okay? What happened?

1022
01:31:23.103 --> 01:31:24.735
You have to leave right now.

1023
01:31:24.751 --> 01:31:26.549
- What happened?
- Those eyes!

1024
01:31:26.574 --> 01:31:29.729
Those horrible yellow eyes!

1025
01:31:35.412 --> 01:31:37.307
He knows who I am.

1026
01:32:21.917 --> 01:32:23.378
I'm sorry.

1027
01:32:27.356 --> 01:32:29.776
- Will she be okay?
- She'll be fine.

1028
01:32:29.801 --> 01:32:31.620
She's been sleeping all day.

1029
01:32:33.512 --> 01:32:35.182
Thanks for coming.

1030
01:32:35.207 --> 01:32:36.385
Of course.

1031
01:32:40.435 --> 01:32:43.497
How are you?
You okay about the other night?

1032
01:32:43.522 --> 01:32:47.338
Yeah. I'm fine. I just felt bad
about leaving Aunt May.

1033
01:32:47.363 --> 01:32:48.858
Have you talked to Harry?

1034
01:32:48.882 --> 01:32:50.325
He called me.

1035
01:32:50.863 --> 01:32:53.031
I haven't called him back.

1036
01:32:55.117 --> 01:32:56.745
The fact is...

1037
01:32:58.370 --> 01:33:00.057
I'm in love with somebody else.

1038
01:33:00.082 --> 01:33:00.946
You are?

1039
01:33:00.971 --> 01:33:02.674
At least I think I am.

1040
01:33:04.736 --> 01:33:06.358
It's not the time to talk about it.

1041
01:33:06.383 --> 01:33:08.026
No. no. Go on.

1042
01:33:08.051 --> 01:33:10.760
Would I know his name. this guy?

1043
01:33:11.487 --> 01:33:14.026
You'll think I'm a little girl
with a crush.

1044
01:33:14.493 --> 01:33:15.869
Trust me.

1045
01:33:16.221 --> 01:33:17.472
It's funny.

1046
01:33:19.482 --> 01:33:23.445
He's saved my life twice.
and I've never even seen his face.

1047
01:33:23.477 --> 01:33:25.151
Oh. Him.

1048
01:33:25.671 --> 01:33:27.166
You're laughing at me.

1049
01:33:27.185 --> 01:33:30.319
No. I understand. He is extremely cool.

1050
01:33:30.344 --> 01:33:33.346
But do you think it's true.
all the terrible things they say about him?

1051
01:33:33.378 --> 01:33:37.743
No. no. Not Spider-Man.
not a chance in the world.

1052
01:33:37.825 --> 01:33:39.452
I know him a little bit.

1053
01:33:39.745 --> 01:33:42.623
I'm sort of his unofficial photographer.

1054
01:33:42.974 --> 01:33:44.799
Has he mentioned me?

1055
01:33:45.257 --> 01:33:46.227
Yeah.

1056
01:33:46.252 --> 01:33:47.711
What'd he say?

1057
01:33:48.378 --> 01:33:49.713
I said...

1058
01:33:50.797 --> 01:33:55.093
He asked me what I thought about you.

1059
01:33:56.104 --> 01:33:58.057
And what did you say?

1060
01:33:58.764 --> 01:34:03.160
I said. "Spider-Man."

1061
01:34:03.185 --> 01:34:09.816
I said. "The great thing about M.J. is...

1062
01:34:10.734 --> 01:34:13.987
...when you look in her eyes...

1063
01:34:16.532 --> 01:34:19.280
...and she's looking back in yours...

1064
01:34:20.744 --> 01:34:23.747
...everything feels...

1065
01:34:24.957 --> 01:34:26.792
...not quite normal.

1066
01:34:28.043 --> 01:34:32.005
Because you feel stronger...

1067
01:34:33.549 --> 01:34:37.177
...and weaker at the same time.

1068
01:34:38.303 --> 01:34:43.296
You feel excited...
and at the same time...

1069
01:34:43.892 --> 01:34:45.519
...terrified.

1070
01:34:47.855 --> 01:34:52.150
The truth is. you don't know
what you feel...

1071
01:34:53.569 --> 01:34:56.452
...except you know what kind of man
you want to be.

1072
01:34:59.830 --> 01:35:01.707
It's as if you've...

1073
01:35:02.403 --> 01:35:05.573
...reached the unreachable...

1074
01:35:07.165 --> 01:35:09.609
...and you weren't ready for it."

1075
01:35:13.338 --> 01:35:15.090
You said that?

1076
01:35:15.852 --> 01:35:18.187
Well. something like that.

1077
01:36:02.395 --> 01:36:03.896
Dad?

1078
01:36:09.251 --> 01:36:11.336
Dad. is that you?

1079
01:36:17.863 --> 01:36:19.365
What is it?

1080
01:36:21.782 --> 01:36:25.729
You were right about M.J.
You're right about everything.

1081
01:36:27.788 --> 01:36:29.549
She's in love with Peter.

1082
01:36:30.791 --> 01:36:31.983
Parker?

1083
01:36:32.007 --> 01:36:32.780
Yeah.

1084
01:36:32.805 --> 01:36:35.190
And how does he feel about her?

1085
01:36:37.219 --> 01:36:39.764
He's loved her since the 4th grade.

1086
01:36:40.801 --> 01:36:45.306
He pretends like he doesn't. but
there's no one Peter cares for more.

1087
01:36:48.866 --> 01:36:50.617
I'm so sorry.

1088
01:36:53.125 --> 01:36:55.391
I haven't always been there for you.
have I?

1089
01:36:58.402 --> 01:37:01.641
You're busy. You're an important man.
I understand.

1090
01:37:01.666 --> 01:37:03.501
That's no excuse.

1091
01:37:04.475 --> 01:37:06.269
I'm proud of you.

1092
01:37:06.833 --> 01:37:10.937
I've lost sight of that somewhere.
But I'll make it up to you. Harry.

1093
01:37:11.999 --> 01:37:15.391
I'm going to rectify certain inequities.

1094
01:37:29.391 --> 01:37:31.185
Wake up. little spider.

1095
01:37:31.210 --> 01:37:32.712
Wake up.

1096
01:37:34.195 --> 01:37:35.779
Go home. dear.

1097
01:37:35.957 --> 01:37:37.292
You look awful.

1098
01:37:37.524 --> 01:37:39.960
- And you look beautiful.
- Thank you.

1099
01:37:39.985 --> 01:37:43.345
- I don't like to leave you here.
- But I'm safe here.

1100
01:37:43.488 --> 01:37:46.290
- Can I do anything for you?
- You do too much.

1101
01:37:46.315 --> 01:37:50.852
College. a job. all this time with me.
You're not Superman. you know.

1102
01:37:52.664 --> 01:37:54.509
A smile. Finally.

1103
01:37:54.534 --> 01:37:57.985
Haven't seen one of those on your face
since Mary Jane was here.

1104
01:37:58.010 --> 01:38:01.118
Hey. You were supposed to be asleep.

1105
01:38:02.153 --> 01:38:07.118
You know. you were about 6 years old
when M.J.'s family moved in next door.

1106
01:38:07.143 --> 01:38:11.298
When she got out of the car.
and you saw her for the first time.

1107
01:38:11.323 --> 01:38:17.580
you grabbed me and said.
"Aunt May. is that an angel?"

1108
01:38:17.856 --> 01:38:19.572
Gee. did I say that?

1109
01:38:19.585 --> 01:38:21.402
You sure did.

1110
01:38:23.981 --> 01:38:28.899
Well. Harry's in love with her.
She's still his girl.

1111
01:38:28.924 --> 01:38:30.681
Well. isn't that up to her?

1112
01:38:30.869 --> 01:38:33.586
She doesn't really know who I am.

1113
01:38:33.616 --> 01:38:35.657
Because you won't let her.

1114
01:38:35.682 --> 01:38:38.501
You're so mysterious all the time.

1115
01:38:39.098 --> 01:38:45.821
Tell me. would it be so dangerous to
let Mary Jane know how much you care?

1116
01:38:46.552 --> 01:38:49.032
Everybody else knows.

1117
01:38:52.023 --> 01:38:53.415
I'll be right back.

1118
01:38:53.844 --> 01:38:55.137
But...

1119
01:39:02.409 --> 01:39:04.411
Come on. pick up.

1120
01:39:04.522 --> 01:39:06.782
- Hey. M.J.
- Hi. Sing your song at the beep.

1121
01:39:09.032 --> 01:39:11.076
M.J.. it's Peter. You there?

1122
01:39:11.266 --> 01:39:13.649
Hello? You there?

1123
01:39:14.627 --> 01:39:18.587
I'm just calling to check up on you.
Will you call me when you get in?

1124
01:39:19.282 --> 01:39:20.700
All right. well...

1125
01:39:21.101 --> 01:39:22.144
Don't...

1126
01:39:22.944 --> 01:39:25.032
Don't go up any dark alleys.

1127
01:39:25.465 --> 01:39:26.415
Hello?

1128
01:39:29.440 --> 01:39:33.152
Can Spider-Man come out to play?

1129
01:39:33.177 --> 01:39:34.845
Where is she?

1130
01:40:21.313 --> 01:40:23.165
- What is that?
- That's cool!

1131
01:40:23.190 --> 01:40:27.819
The itsy-bitsy spider
Went up the water spout

1132
01:40:27.892 --> 01:40:32.063
Down came the goblin
And took the spider out

1133
01:40:49.044 --> 01:40:50.795
Goblin. what have you done?

1134
01:41:33.114 --> 01:41:37.350
Spider-Man!
This is why only fools are heroes.

1135
01:41:37.375 --> 01:41:43.897
Because you never know when some lunatic
will come along with a sadistic choice:

1136
01:41:45.116 --> 01:41:47.819
Let die the woman you love...

1137
01:41:52.054 --> 01:41:57.143
...or suffer the little children.

1138
01:41:59.481 --> 01:42:01.600
- Spider-Man!
- Save us!

1139
01:42:02.539 --> 01:42:04.319
Save us!

1140
01:42:05.036 --> 01:42:11.298
Make your choice. Spider-Man.
and see how a hero is rewarded.

1141
01:42:11.323 --> 01:42:13.256
Don't do it. Goblin!

1142
01:42:13.545 --> 01:42:16.465
We are who we choose to be.

1143
01:42:16.731 --> 01:42:17.952
Now. choose!

1144
01:42:17.977 --> 01:42:19.152
No!

1145
01:42:48.335 --> 01:42:49.920
Everybody stay still!

1146
01:42:59.343 --> 01:43:00.864
Ahoy up there!

1147
01:43:00.889 --> 01:43:03.976
We're gonna bring the barge
right under you.

1148
01:43:11.351 --> 01:43:12.855
He's coming back!

1149
01:43:12.879 --> 01:43:15.480
Listen. I need you to climb down.

1150
01:43:15.505 --> 01:43:17.187
- I can't.
- Yes. you can!

1151
01:43:22.244 --> 01:43:25.289
M.J.. you can do it. You have to.

1152
01:43:25.314 --> 01:43:26.757
Trust me.

1153
01:43:28.542 --> 01:43:31.629
Hold on tight and go quickly.

1154
01:43:36.504 --> 01:43:37.539
Hurry!

1155
01:43:37.563 --> 01:43:38.944
I can't. I can't do it.

1156
01:43:38.969 --> 01:43:40.637
Hang on. Mary Jane!

1157
01:44:08.979 --> 01:44:10.154
He's not gonna make it.

1158
01:44:10.178 --> 01:44:11.407
He's gonna make it!

1159
01:44:21.595 --> 01:44:23.611
It's time to die.

1160
01:44:31.807 --> 01:44:34.233
Come on up here! 
I got a little something for you!

1161
01:44:34.254 --> 01:44:35.792
We ought to kick your freaking ass!

1162
01:44:35.817 --> 01:44:39.413
Leave Spider-Man alone!
You gotta pick on a guy saving kids?

1163
01:44:40.327 --> 01:44:43.550
I got something for your ass! You mess
with Spidey. you mess with New York!

1164
01:44:43.575 --> 01:44:46.405
You mess with one of us.
you mess with all of us!

1165
01:44:59.633 --> 01:45:01.426
Spider-Man. watch out!

1166
01:45:33.292 --> 01:45:37.389
Misery. misery. misery.
That's what you've chosen.

1167
01:45:38.463 --> 01:45:43.135
I offered you friendship...
and you spat in my face.

1168
01:46:34.228 --> 01:46:37.676
You've spun your last web. Spider-Man.

1169
01:46:38.065 --> 01:46:43.237
Had you not been so selfish. your
girlfriend's death would have been quick.

1170
01:46:43.262 --> 01:46:51.864
But now that you've really pissed me off.
I'm gonna finish her nice and slow.

1171
01:46:56.542 --> 01:46:58.129
M.J. and I.

1172
01:46:59.419 --> 01:47:02.714
we're gonna have a hell of a time.

1173
01:47:56.502 --> 01:47:58.045
Peter. stop!

1174
01:47:58.298 --> 01:48:00.502
Stop! It's me.

1175
01:48:09.710 --> 01:48:11.010
Mr. Osborn.

1176
01:48:11.035 --> 01:48:12.861
Peter. thank God for you.

1177
01:48:13.091 --> 01:48:15.427
You killed those people
on that balcony.

1178
01:48:15.452 --> 01:48:18.072
The Goblin killed!
I had nothing to do with it!

1179
01:48:18.297 --> 01:48:20.588
Don't let him take me again.

1180
01:48:20.613 --> 01:48:22.657
I beg you. Protect me.

1181
01:48:22.947 --> 01:48:26.648
You tried to kill Aunt May.
You tried to kill Mary Jane.

1182
01:48:26.673 --> 01:48:28.175
But not you.

1183
01:48:28.842 --> 01:48:32.804
I tried to stop it. But I couldn't stop it.

1184
01:48:32.829 --> 01:48:34.914
I would never hurt you.

1185
01:48:35.213 --> 01:48:37.132
I knew from the beginning.

1186
01:48:37.469 --> 01:48:42.773
if anything ever happened to me.
it was you I could count on.

1187
01:48:42.798 --> 01:48:46.267
You. Peter Parker. would save me.
and so you have.

1188
01:48:46.777 --> 01:48:48.612
Thank God for you.

1189
01:48:49.534 --> 01:48:50.952
Give me your hand.

1190
01:48:52.115 --> 01:48:55.494
Believe in me as I believed in you.

1191
01:48:56.756 --> 01:48:59.119
I've been like a father to you.

1192
01:49:01.273 --> 01:49:03.010
Be a son to me now.

1193
01:49:04.790 --> 01:49:06.666
I have a father.

1194
01:49:07.448 --> 01:49:09.799
His name was Ben Parker.

1195
01:49:11.773 --> 01:49:13.232
Godspeed. Spider-Man.

1196
01:49:32.012 --> 01:49:32.971
Peter.

1197
01:49:35.997 --> 01:49:37.832
Don't tell Harry.

1198
01:50:09.657 --> 01:50:11.142
What have you done?

1199
01:50:11.392 --> 01:50:12.977
What have you done?!

1200
01:50:40.998 --> 01:50:43.041
I'm so sorry. Harry.

1201
01:50:44.029 --> 01:50:46.773
I know what it's like to lose a father.

1202
01:50:49.483 --> 01:50:52.778
I didn't lose him.
He was stolen from me.

1203
01:50:54.246 --> 01:50:56.540
One day Spider-Man will pay.

1204
01:50:58.534 --> 01:51:01.492
I swear on my father's grave.
Spider-Man will pay.

1205
01:51:06.800 --> 01:51:08.635
Thank God for you. Peter.

1206
01:51:09.039 --> 01:51:11.242
You're the only family I have.

1207
01:51:36.000 --> 01:51:41.327
<i>No matter what I do.
no matter how hard I try...</i>

1208
01:51:42.134 --> 01:51:46.392
<i>...the ones I love 
will always be the ones who pay.</i>

1209
01:51:56.925 --> 01:51:59.261
You must miss him so much.

1210
01:52:00.133 --> 01:52:02.283
It's been so hard without him.

1211
01:52:06.185 --> 01:52:08.767
There's something
I've been wanting to tell you.

1212
01:52:10.691 --> 01:52:12.484
When I was up there...

1213
01:52:13.400 --> 01:52:15.720
...and I thought I was gonna die...

1214
01:52:17.617 --> 01:52:20.509
...there was only one person
who I was thinking of.

1215
01:52:22.951 --> 01:52:25.556
And it wasn't who I thought it'd be.

1216
01:52:27.364 --> 01:52:29.423
It was you. Pete.

1217
01:52:30.886 --> 01:52:32.762
I kept thinking:

1218
01:52:33.274 --> 01:52:35.877
"I hope I make it through this...

1219
01:52:37.459 --> 01:52:41.180
...so I can see Peter Parker's face
one more time."

1220
01:52:43.222 --> 01:52:44.723
Really?

1221
01:52:45.098 --> 01:52:50.180
There's only one man
who's always been there for me...

1222
01:52:52.147 --> 01:52:57.501
...who makes me feel like 
I'm more than I ever thought I could be.

1223
01:53:00.350 --> 01:53:02.019
That I'm just...

1224
01:53:02.624 --> 01:53:04.055
...me.

1225
01:53:05.170 --> 01:53:06.899
And that's okay.

1226
01:53:09.120 --> 01:53:10.580
The truth is...

1227
01:53:12.824 --> 01:53:14.399
I love you.

1228
01:53:16.752 --> 01:53:18.790
I love you so much. Peter.

1229
01:53:39.454 --> 01:53:43.919
<i>All I wanted was to tell her
how much I loved her.</i>

1230
01:53:44.267 --> 01:53:46.185
I can't...

1231
01:53:48.508 --> 01:53:50.145
You can't what?

1232
01:53:51.248 --> 01:53:52.708
Tell you...

1233
01:53:54.418 --> 01:53:58.755
...everything.
I mean. there's so much to tell.

1234
01:53:59.840 --> 01:54:03.760
Yeah. There's so much to tell.

1235
01:54:04.545 --> 01:54:06.505
I want you to know...

1236
01:54:07.125 --> 01:54:09.795
...that I will always be there for you.

1237
01:54:10.161 --> 01:54:13.278
I will always be there to take care of you.

1238
01:54:15.022 --> 01:54:16.880
I promise you that.

1239
01:54:20.194 --> 01:54:22.487
I will always be your friend.

1240
01:54:25.305 --> 01:54:29.632
Only a friend. Peter Parker?

1241
01:54:31.872 --> 01:54:34.098
That's all I have to give.

1242
01:55:00.977 --> 01:55:06.965
<i>Whatever life holds in store for me.
I will never forget these words:</i>

1243
01:55:06.990 --> 01:55:11.635
<i>"With great power
comes great responsibility."</i>

1244
01:55:12.008 --> 01:55:14.260
<i>This is my gift.</i>

1245
01:55:14.513 --> 01:55:16.424
<i>My curse.</i>

1246
01:55:17.008 --> 01:55:18.713
<i>Who am I?</i>

1247
01:55:19.545 --> 01:55:20.921
<i>I'm Spider-Man.</i>

